race.comment: GIAPPONESE (1) followed a narrow win two back at Ballina with a barnstorming victory at cricket score odds over the mile here a fortnight ago. Progressive colt who looks ideally placed out to this trip so the hat trick is alive. VALOURI (8) missed the top three for the first time when sixth in the GIAPPONESE race here recently. Ground away that day in a run that suggested this longer trip will probably suit. NORTH POLE (2) led but was swamped by GIAPPONESE and others here last start. That was his first run for a month so expect a bit more resistance this time. Last start maiden winner TACITLY (4) is progressing in good style and won't be out of place in this field.
